modules.description: Provides functions to read from and write to file descriptors using Bigarray arrays, and to convert between file descriptors and integers. Handles file system statistics with error handling for safe operations. Supports low-level file manipulation and system call wrappers for reliable I/O and directory changes.

Provides functions to retrieve and manipulate FUSE context, process commands, and manage FUSE operations. Works with opaque FUSE and command structures, along with operation name records. Used to initialize FUSE mounts, handle read operations, and track FUSE process status.

Checks if an opaque value is null, returns an undefined value, and manages a FUSE loop execution. It operates on opaque FUSE types, strings, and function signatures with optional names. It is used to handle FUSE operation naming and lifecycle management in file system implementations.

Provides functions to transform, chain, and inspect values wrapped in a 'a result type, which represents either a successful value or an error. Supports operations like mapping over successes, handling errors, and combining results in sequence. Used to manage error-prone computations in file system operations, ensuring safe propagation of failures.

Provides functions for mounting file systems, handling file operations, and managing concurrent access. Works with file system nodes, file descriptors, and thread-safe data structures. Used to implement custom file systems on macOS with support for multi-threaded operations.

manages file I/O and FUSE operations through low-level file descriptor manipulation, context handling, and result-based error management. It supports reading/writing with Bigarray, FUSE command processing, and safe error propagation using result types. Functions include converting file descriptors to integers, initializing FUSE mounts, and handling FUSE loop execution. It enables building robust file systems with reliable I/O, command handling, and error-aware computation flows.
